As a child, Lubitz is said to have always wanted to be a pilot and covered his bedroom walls with pictures of planes and collected model aircraft.

He is also said to have visited an airfield just 30 miles from the site of the tragic crash with his gliding club as a child.

Among the 150 victims of the crash were 16 German children from the same exchange class at school and three Britons - one of which was just seven months old. 

German officials have announced there will be a ceremony on April 17 in Cologne Cathedral attended by German Chancellor Angela Merkel and senior officials from other countries including France and Spain.

 

 

 

